page_title: Expand Electric Trolley Bus Service - Seattle Area
aduiance:
Public group  · 322 membersWe won the first half of this battle--saving clean, quiet, fiscally sustainable bus service in King County. We won't lose what we have or waste the capital investments we've made in electric trolley bus (ETB) infrastructure. The old Gillig and Breda trolleys have all been replaced with new ones that have air conditioning, battery backup, low-floor boarding, use 25% less energy, and let riders exit the back doors without yelling "Back Door!"
Now we have to move from defense into offense mode--expanding and improving ETB service, replacing more diesel bus routes with ETBs, and advocating that new routes Metro creates be electric whenever possible. This is especially important as Seattle and King County expand the Rapid Ride network. We must stay active and involved to make our transit network the cleanest, quietest, most fiscally sustainable it can be.8 posts a year|Public group  · 322 members
